               Ireland was almoſt all revolted ſoon after the death of the King; 
                  year 1649 only the

City of Dublin held out for the Parliament: But Cromwel going over thither about September 1649. in leſs then a years time reduces that whole Kingdom to the obedience of the Parliament, driving the Natives for the moſt part out, and cooping up the reſt in the Weſtern parts of the Kingdom.
